@flexiarg enrichment/extend-not-rewrite
@title Extend, Don't Rewrite
@sigils [节/本]
@keywords extend, rewrite, reuse, existing, script, I-4, read-before-write
@audience futon developers, enrichment operators
@tone pragmatic
@factor Keen investigation (dhammavicaya)
@references [stack-coherence/evidence-ledger enrichment/ARGUMENT]

! conclusion:
  When 80% of the required functionality already exists in a tested script,
  add to it rather than writing a replacement.

  + context: Layer 0 of M-futon-enrichment requires namespace topology, git
    churn, and indentation complexity ingested as hyperedges. The existing
    ingest-three-columns.py already handles namespace/var/requires ingestion
    with tested HTTP helpers and error handling.
  + IF:
    The existing ingestion script handles the hard infrastructure (HTTP POST,
    error handling, count verification, EDN parsing) and 80% of the data.
  + HOWEVER:
    It lacks git churn and indentation complexity functions.
  + THEN:
    Add a --layer0 flag and two new functions (~65 lines) to the existing
    script rather than writing a new enrichment-specific script.
  + BECAUSE:
    I-4 (Read Before You Write) — the existing code embeds design decisions
    about endpoint format, penholder auth, error recovery, and verification
    that would need to be re-discovered in a new script. Extension preserves
    these decisions; rewriting discards them.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - evidence: diff of ingest-three-columns.py before/after Layer 0 addition
    - evidence: --layer0 --count output showing new hyperedge types
